cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.PF 

This paper discusses load balancing techniques in data centers, which is a topic related to network infrastructure and communication. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the performance of load balancing schemes, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) or cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper mentions the trade-off between stickiness violation and latency, which could be related to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) or cs.PF (Performance).
